  "prompt": "What are some good movies about a person that has a hidden power that he/she couldn't use until put into a pressure situation?",
  "response": "Here are some great movies that feature characters with hidden powers or abilities that emerge during high-pressure situations:\n\n1. **Chronicle (2012)** - Three high school friends discover a mysterious substance that grants them telekinetic powers. As they experiment with their abilities, the pressure of their circumstances reveals darker aspects of their personalities.\n\n2. **Unbreakable (2000)** - A man discovers he has superhuman abilities after surviving a train crash. The film explores his journey of self-discovery and the emergence of his powers as he confronts a mysterious figure who believes he is a superhero.\n\n3. **Spider-Man: Homecoming (2017)** - Peter Parker grapples with the responsibilities of his newfound powers as Spider-Man. He struggles to balance being a teenager and stepping up as a hero when he's faced with a major threat.\n\n4. **Kick-Ass (2010)** - An ordinary teenager decides to become a superhero, despite having no powers or training. When put in high-stakes situations, he discovers his own potential and draws out unexpected abilities.\n\n5. **Jumper (2008)** - A young man discovers he has the ability to teleport. His powers are revealed under pressure as he navigates a dangerous world filled with those who want to eliminate people like him.\n\n6. **The Matrix (1999)** - Neo, an ordinary computer programmer, discovers he has extraordinary abilities in a simulated reality. His powers are fully realized when he is thrust into a fight against powerful adversaries.\n\n7. **Lucy (2014)** - A woman unknowingly becomes part of a dangerous drug trade. When the drug leaks into her system, it unlocks hidden mental abilities that she learns to use as she confronts various threats.\n\n8. **The Last Airbender (2010)** - A young boy discovers he is the Avatar, capable of bending all four elements. His powers are awakened and evolve as he faces significant challenges in a world divided by war.\n\n9. **The Incredibles (2004)** - A family of superheroes, who have hidden their powers from the world, must come together under pressure to confront a new villain threatening their existence.\n\n10. **X-Men: First Class (2011)** - The film explores the origins of various X-Men characters, showcasing how their hidden powers surface when they face discrimination and danger.\n\nThese films often delve into themes of self-discovery and responsibility, showcasing how immense pressure can bring out one's true potential.",
